Name: intrinsic cardiomyopathy
Definition: A cardiomyopathy that is characterized as weakness in the muscle of the heart that is not due to an identifiable external cause.

Name: extrinsic cardiomyopathy
Definition: A cardiomyopathy that is characterized by the pathology occuring outside of the myocardium.

Name: obsolete cutaneous tuberculosis
Definition: A cardiomyopathy that is characterized by the pathology occuring outside of the myocardium.
Synonym: Tuberculosis of skin and subcutaneous cellular tissue
